<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870911-0089 </DOCNO><HL> Coastal Corp. Unit Finds Gas</HL><DD> 09/11/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CGPNATURAL GAS, PIPELINES (LNG) </IN><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Coastal Corp. said its Coastal Oil andamp; Gas Co. unit discovered natural gas at its Ben Bolt Exploratory Prospect in south Texas.    The company's No. 1 Roger Hoffman well tested at a daily rate of 10.2 million cubic feet of natural gas through a 20/64th-inch choke from a depth of 9,500 feet.    Coastal Oil andamp; Gas operates the well and owns a 50% interest. Double Oil andamp; Gas Inc. owns the other half interest. Double is controlled by a private investor, whom a Coastal spokesman declined to identify. </TEXT></DOC>